body:
We should add support for Android Studio 4.0 once it comes out of Canary (support Beta and on). cc @stevemessick 

https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/issues/4136 (and related) for context

comment_data.body: @stevemessick - is this likely for this milestone?
Yes, I think it will be required.
Is that related to IntelliJ IDEA 2020? Because the plugin is also incompatible with the latest EAP of IntelliJ IDEA.

Android Studio 4 was just released. Is there an ETA on when the flutter plugin will support 4.0? When I click Check for Updates in Android Studio, this is what I see:

![Screen Shot 2020-05-28 at 13 48 19](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/31281983/83175471-ee0ee880-a0e9-11ea-9d9f-4f1216a1ce78.png)
Can you try updated and restarting? You may then see a prompt about new plugin versions being available.
Oh, you're right; that worked! Thanks!

> Android Studio 4 was just released. Is there an ETA on when the flutter plugin will support 4.0? When I click Check for Updates in Android Studio, this is what I see:

title: Support Android Studio 4.0
